# PARABLE — Cursor Rules

## PARABLE Technical Standards (Feltus Frequency Protocol)

These standards apply to **all** PARABLE features (live stream, Shed, Testify, altar, maps, onboarding)—not only games. When product logic feels generic, **raise density**: add **Mist** (blur/backdrop), **Glow** (neon cyan/gold accents), and **Haptics** (`navigator.vibrate` where appropriate) so interactions feel spiritual-data-rich, not flat.

### Visual language

- **Mist**: Layered blur, depth, and gradient “atmosphere” (glass, fog, volumetric cues)—never only flat solid panels for primary worship/live UI.
- **Glow**: Neon highlights on key actions (cyan `#00f2ff` family, gold/amber for “Glory” / peak moments). Signal importance with light, not only color.
- **Haptics**: Pair major moments (Amen, praise break, altar commit, streak) with short vibration patterns; respect `navigator.vibrate` availability and user settings.

### Glory Pulse (signals)

- **Every meaningful Kingdom interaction** (Amen, Shout, score, commit, seed, bucket, etc.) should emit a **Signal** toward **Supabase Realtime** (or a dedicated `global_pulse` / `activity_log` style channel) so the network can react in real time.
- Prefer **one clear write path** (table insert + broadcast) over ad-hoc client-only state for events that should be visible globally or in-room.

### Quantum entanglement (sync)

- **Room state** (BPM, praise break, metronome tick, altar phase) must stay **synchronized** across clients: same animation phase at the same millisecond when possible—use **shared clocks** (server time, host authority, or Realtime broadcast), not independent `setInterval` per tab.
- **LiveKit** is the default for **ultra-low-latency** audio/video (Shed, jam sessions); target **<100ms** feel for music. **WebRTC** patterns, not consumer HLS delay, for real-time jamming.

### Imago standards

- **Avatars**: Prefer **3D GLB**, rigged for **praise moves**; avoid treating avatars as static icons when the feature is worship/live presence.
- **Auras**: Tie visual intensity to **Supabase** fields such as `anointing_level`, `aura_type`, streaks—e.g. stronger glow / particle density as level or streak rises.

### Praise Break Engine (live stream module — target behavior)

- **Detection**: Web Audio API for BPM; treat **~140–170 BPM** “shout” band as candidate **Praise Break**; drive `isPraiseBreakActive`.
- **Visuals**: While active—camera shake / shader on video, **gold/cyan strobe** overlay (tasteful, performance-aware).
- **Haptics**: Optional kick-sync vibration on supported devices.
- **Multiplayer**: Host “Shout” should trigger **Supabase Realtime** so all **Imago** avatars in the room play **synced** praise animations (e.g. `praise_dance_01`).

### Shed Room (musician hub)

- Use **`@livekit/components-react`** for rooms; **high-fidelity audio** (e.g. Opus 48kHz where configured).
- **Shared metronome / BPM**: `useMetronome`-style hook + Realtime so BPM changes propagate; haptics may follow host beat.
- **Director toggle**: optional focus cameras (fretboard, keys), PiP; **request-to-join** queue in Supabase for promoting Member → Musician.
- **Stripe / Seeds gate**: Before mounting `LiveKitRoom`, check **event access** (e.g. `event_access`); if no paid “Shed Pass,” route to merch / sow flow.

### Digital Altar Call

- **Trigger**: `isAltarCallActive`; UI shifts from high-BPM praise to **low-BPM, heavy atmosphere** (royal purple + gold, slower mist).
- **Interaction**: Long-press **commit** with **Presence meter** + low-frequency continuous haptic; log to Supabase (e.g. `altar_commits`).
- **Follow-up**: AI chaplain / mentor thread hooks via RPC or webhook when specified by product.

### Global Signal Array / Global Pulse

- **Global map**: `@react-three/fiber` + globe; on **Realtime** `global_pulse` / `activity_log` inserts, spawn **Glory Sparks** (particles) from **lat/long** when available.
- **Mist shader**: Global mist density can track **recent activity volume** (e.g. last 60s)—more activity = thicker **golden** mist.
- **Ticker**: Optional “Neural Download” / personnel ticker for recent global events.

### Onboarding (Binary Ark / Activation Portal)

- Post sign-up: **seed grant** (e.g. 100 seeds), **Framer Motion** progress, **Supabase RPC** to init `user_seeds` / `anointing_level`—copy tone: welcoming, “Second Outpouring” atmosphere, not corporate boilerplate.

### AI Architect (Shed / stream)

- Optional: Web Audio buffer → pitch/chord detection → **Nashville-style** chord JSON → `session_charts` in Supabase; display **live chord** for members.

---

## Pro prompt (when code feels too plain)

If the user says **“Remember the Feltus Frequency—more Glory”**—add mist, glow, haptics, and Realtime hooks without bloating unrelated files; keep changes tied to the feature at hand.

---

# PARABLE Gaming Standards

These rules apply when building or extending **PARABLE game modules** (The Narrow Road, Kingdom Hoops, Gridiron Glory, Sanctuary 3D, engine lab). For non-game UI (feed, auth, settings), standard Next.js/React patterns apply—**plus** the Feltus Frequency standards above where worship/atmosphere matters.

## Rendering (GPU-first)

- **Do not** add new **2D Canvas** or **HTML/CSS-driven game logic** (simulation loop, collision resolution, scoring) for PARABLE games. Use the **3D engine path** instead.
- **Always use** `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei` for new 3D scenes and helpers.
- **Prefer WebGPU** via the existing bootstrap (`src/components/engine/createParableRenderer.ts` + `three/webgpu`); **fallback** to WebGL when init fails.
- Use **PBR-style materials** (`MeshStandardMaterial` / `MeshPhysicalMaterial`, roughness/metalness, env lighting) so metal, skin, and fabric read as high-fidelity—not flat `MeshBasicMaterial` unless debug-only.

## Physics

- **Use Rapier** via `@react-three/rapier` for **new** 3D gameplay (gravity, rigid bodies, collisions). Wire the physics world to the same frame loop as R3F (`useFrame` / fixed timestep pattern).
- Outcomes that should feel “real” (ball, rim, tackles, shields) must come from **physics contact**, not timer bars alone.

## Characters & assets

- **Characters are rigged 3D meshes** loaded as **GLB/glTF** (`useGLTF` / GLTFLoader), not 2D sprites or CSS shapes.
- Avatar/loadout data is sourced from **Supabase** (see `supabase/schema-gaming-2026.sql`: `imago_inventory`, `world_influence`, etc.) and hydrated into the scene.

## Input

- Implement **Pro-Stick–style analog logic** for sports and action: accumulate **gamepad + pointer** samples per frame; map to direction, magnitude, and release windows (2K/Madden-style), not only `onClick` for core mechanics.

## Multiplayer & state

- **Game state** that must sync across clients (presence, inventory, session scores, world position) should use **Supabase Realtime** (and/or authoritative writes via Edge/RPC for anti-cheat). Do not rely on client-only `localStorage` for competitive truth.

## Legacy exception (until migrated)

- Existing **2D canvas prototypes** under `src/components/games/*` and `/gaming/play/*` remain until explicitly rebuilt in 3D. **Do not extend** them with new mechanics; **prefer** new work in `src/components/engine/` and routes under `/play/engine` (or successor 3D routes).

## “Hard reset” migration direction

When rewriting a module from 2D to AAA 3D: **Scene + PerspectiveCamera**, **Rapier world**, **third-person follow camera**, **Pointer Lock** where appropriate for look, **3DPlayer** loading GLB from Supabase—not a colored `fillRect` grid.
